<div class="container-fluid my-4 no-print">
    <div class="card p-4 shadow">
        <InputGroupTitle Title="Step-by-Step Assembly Workflow"
                         Subtitle="Guided Process for Efficient Belt Assembly"
                         Description="Follow these steps to navigate the assembly process seamlessly. Each step is designed to ensure accurate configurations, proper material selections, and alignment techniques for optimal results in creating modular belt systems." />

        <!-- Button to open modal -->
        <div class="text-center mb-4">
            <button class="btn btn-dark btn-lg" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#assemblyWorkflowModal">View Assembly Workflow</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Modal for Step-by-Step Assembly Workflow -->
<div class="modal fade" id="assemblyWorkflowModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="assemblyWorkflowModalLabel" aria-hidden="true" >
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="assemblyWorkflowModalLabel">Step-by-Step Assembly Workflow</h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <!-- Workflow Badges -->
                <div class="container mb-4 text-center">
                    <span class="badge text-bg-secondary">AutoCAD LT</span>
                    <span class="badge text-bg-warning">SolidWorks</span>
                    <span class="badge text-bg-danger">PTC Creo</span>
                    <span class="badge text-bg-secondary">Windchill</span>
                    <span class="badge text-bg-success">DraftSite</span>
                </div>

                <!-- Step-by-Step Flow -->
                <!-- Step 1: Getting Started -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">1. Getting Started</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Understand Material Requirements:</strong> Review materials list and drawing parameters to get specifications like module types (edge, mid, roller, griptop), link counts, and dimensions.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Identify Needed Blocks:</strong> Create a list of standard AutoCAD blocks for each belt type, including edge modules, mid modules, and accessories.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2">
                                <strong>Block Categories:</strong> Define blocks for:
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Edge Modules:</strong> Separate blocks for left and right edges.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Mid Modules:</strong> Blocks with various link counts.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Accessories:</strong> Blocks for rollers, grip tops, and flights.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 2: Setting Up Blocks and Origins -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">2. Setting Up Blocks and Origins</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Define Strategic Origins:</strong> Set insertion points for each block to simplify alignment.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Add Constraints:</strong> Use constraints to ensure proper alignment and interlocking.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Universal Naming Convention:</strong> Use systematic block names (e.g., <code>M1220_Edge_L</code>, <code>M1220_Mid_6Links</code>) for easy searching and organization.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 3: AutoCAD Command Workflow -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">3. AutoCAD Command Workflow</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Insert and Align Modules:</strong> Use <code>INSERT</code> to place blocks and <code>ALIGN</code> to adjust position.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Pattern and Array:</strong> Use <code>ARRAY</code> to repeat mid modules along the belt’s length.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Interlocking Modules:</strong> Snap and apply constraints to ensure interlocking of modules.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Adjust for Cuts:</strong> Use <code>TRIM</code> to adjust modules that need trimming.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 4: Configuring Belt Dimensions and Part Counts -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">4. Belt Assembly</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Equation-Based Configuration:</strong> Use formulas to automatically adjust belt dimensions.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Custom Properties:</strong> Apply properties for modifications like part numbers, material, etc.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Cut List Generation:</strong> Develop a table in AutoCAD for noting module counts and specific cuts.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 5: Finalizing the Model and 2D Drawing -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">5. Finalizing the Model and 2D Drawing</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Create Standard Views:</strong> Set up top and side views with dimensions and callouts.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Add Annotations:</strong> Label critical points, including interlocking and cut areas.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Export:</strong> Use standard templates for consistent layout and fields like project name and dimensions.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 6: Quality Control and Review -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">6. Quality Control and Review</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Check Interlocks:</strong> Ensure each module interlocks with its neighboring module.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Verify Dimensions:</strong> Confirm all dimensions match specifications.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Save as Template:</strong> Save as a template for future use to streamline workflow.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 7: Universal Methodology for Other Belts -->
                <div class="card step mb-3">
                    <h5 class="card-title card-header">7. Universal Methodology for Other Belts</h5>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Adjust for Different Belt Series:</strong> Apply the same methodology with adjustments for other series (e.g., M1230, M1280).</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item p-2"><strong>Framework Consistency:</strong> Use standardized naming and alignment across belt types.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
